hopobject.body: Do you have any exams coming up? celexa pill image A clear path forward is now, finally, starting to emerge on climate change. The Clean Air Act allows White House and State Department officials to negotiate bilaterally with China on significant greenhouse gas cuts. And if China and the United States – which, together, represent 40 percent of the world's emissions – can agree, then it is unlikely that others will stand in the way at this juncture in history. We won't need an international treaty.
